Richard Warren CLARK, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 21220. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. June 5, 1964. Richard W. Clark, pro se. Edgar L. Jenkins, Asst. U. S. Atty., Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before TUTTLE, Chief Judge, BROWN, Circuit Judge, and BREWSTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM:

The appeal in this Section 2255 case is clearly without merit. The judgment is Affirmed.
